                <p>House music originated in the 1980s in Chicago, blending disco, electronic dance music, and soul influences. Characterized by repetitive beats, synthesized sounds, and soulful vocals, it encapsulates a sense of freedom and community. With its global reach, house music remains a staple in clubs, festivals, and playlists worldwide.</p>
